Description: Entrepreneurship is thriving even in this market. Take a look at some promising new companies with fellow alums as part of MIT Angels. MIT
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Entrepreneurship is thriving even in this market.  Take a look at some promising new companies with fellow alums as part of "MIT Angels".  MIT Angels are interested and engaged in the start-up community and committed to investing their time and money into new, cutting edge, early stage businesses.  Our group is made up of individuals with broad experience in technology, semiconductor, energy, general management, entrepreneurship, finance, consulting and law. The involvement of the group in portfolio companies will vary from deal to deal. Entrepreneurs will have access to the group for general advice and direct involvement by individual members where we can make a difference. Potential roles for MIT Angels include “money only investor”, Board member, CEO mentor and advisor/consultant. Our group meets on a quarterly basis and invite three startups per meeting that can benefit either from advice or investment as they seek angel investors (with a preference for companies started by MIT alum entrepreneurs).   The Deal Selection Team evaluates more than 50 business plans to select the 3 presenting companies.  Entrepreneurs can expect a thorough examination and, occasionally, an investment from some of Silicon Valley's most accomplished entrepreneurs. We strongly encourage business plan submissions from MIT Alumni, but consider all investments based on potential economic returns.
